<subSubSection id="C32A6541FFC16F07FF6FF9360B3A1A67" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8F36CAFFC16F07FF6FF9360B3A1A67" blockId="0.[151,1436,1480,1845]" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">
<emphasis id="B944EAD8FFC16F07FF6FF9360E0D1BF8" bold="true" box="[199,317,1683,1706]" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Morphologically, the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D49FFC16F07FD05F9370CA21BF8" authority="Daniel" authorityName="Daniel The" authorityYear="1954" box="[685,914,1682,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Microlithosia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B944EAD8FFC16F07FD05F9370C0D1BF8" box="[685,829,1682,1706]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Microlithosia</emphasis>
Daniel
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D49FFC16F07FC08F9370BC71BF8" authority="Dubatolov &amp; Kishida" authorityName="Dubatolov &amp; Kishida" box="[928,1271,1682,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Bucsekia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B944EAD8FFC16F07FC08F9370B301BF8" box="[928,1024,1682,1706]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Bucsekia</emphasis>
Dubatolov &amp; Kishida
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D49FFC16F07FA9BF9360FEB1B9E" authority="De Freina" authorityName="De Freina" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Wittia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B944EAD8FFC16F07FA9BF9360A431BF8" box="[1331,1395,1683,1706]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Wittia</emphasis>
De Freina
</taxonomicName>
are small, generally yellowish or orange, and can only be distinguished on the basis of male genitalia. The most striking character of 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D49FFC16F07FEDDF9720D351BBD" authorityName="Daniel The" authorityYear="1954" box="[373,517,1751,1775]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Microlithosia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B944EAD8FFC16F07FEDDF9720D351BBD" box="[373,517,1751,1775]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Microlithosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a long process originating from the aedeagus. The process is apically covered with small spines and is absent in both of its closely related genera. Furthermore, absence of a long process arising from sacculus, directed basally (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D49FFC16F07FE79F8B80D011A67" box="[465,561,1821,1845]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Bucsekia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B944EAD8FFC16F07FE79F8B80D011A67" box="[465,561,1821,1845]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Bucsekia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) also separate 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D49FFC16F07FD79F8B80C511A67" authorityName="Daniel The" authorityYear="1954" box="[721,865,1821,1845]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Microlithosia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B944EAD8FFC16F07FD79F8B80C511A67" box="[721,865,1821,1845]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Microlithosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<emphasis id="B944EAD8FFC16F07FC0AF8B80B3A1A67" box="[930,1034,1821,1845]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">
<taxonomicName id="4C304D49FFC16F07FC0AF8B80B361A67" box="[930,1030,1821,1845]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Bucsekia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Bucsekia</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
